				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$10 \%$$\end{document} and larger, [145]. Especially weakly cross-linked samples require slower heating profiles, hence longer measurement times, and produce inherently larger errors, [143, 146].

